Overall, the character of House was well received;<ref name="dailytelegraph-postrev">{{cite news|author=Davies, Hugh|date=2004-11-20|title=Dr Laurie has viewers of US TV in stitches |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|page=N9}}</ref><ref name="usatoday-review">{{cite news |author=Bianco, Robert|date=2004-11-14| url = http://www.usatoday.com/life/television/reviews/2004-11-15-house_x.htm| title = There's a doctor worth watching in 'House'| work=[[USA Today]] | accessdate = 2006-12-30|page=D1}}</ref> When the show received a [[List of Peabody Award winners (2000-2009)#2005|2005]] [[Peabody Award]], the Peabody board
called Gregory House an "unorthodox lead character – a misanthropic diagnostician"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.broadcastingcable.com/article/CA6322173.html?display=Breaking+News&referral=SUPP&nid=2228://|title=South Park, House Get Peabodys|last=Eggerton|first=John|date=2006-04-05|work=Broadcasting & Cable|publisher=Reed Business Information|accessdate=2008-08-31}}</ref>[[Tom Shales]] of ''The Washington Post'' called House "the most electrifying character to hit television in years".<ref name="washingtonpost-review">{{cite news | author=Shales, Tom|date=2004-11-16 | title = 'House': Watching Is the Best Medicine | work = [[The Washington Post]] || url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A53025-2004Nov15.html | accessdate = 2006-12-30}}</ref> In an Interview with The A.V. club, [[David Morse (actor)|David Morse]], who had a recurring role as [[Michael Tritter|Detective Michael Tritter]] on the show, joked that he now suffers because people come up to him and tell him how much they hate what his character did to House.<ref name="AV">{{cite web |first=Noel |last=Murray |date=2008-06-24|url=http://www.avclub.com/content/feature/random_roles_david_morse?utm_source=imdb_rss_1|title=Random Roles: David Morse|publisher=The A.V. club|accessdate=2008-07-26|subjectlink=David Morse}}</ref> In that same interview Morse said that the character is very beloved.<ref name="AV" /> Nina Smith of TV Guide said that the "sizzling" chemistry of Edelstein and Hugh Laurie keeps the dialogue fresh enough to "warrant a slap on the cheek."<ref name="tvguide">{{cite news|title=Lisa Edelstein Spills Hot House Secrets|url=http://www.tvguide.com/news/house-lisa-edelstein/071120-01|first=Nina Hämmerling|last=Smith|date=2007-11-20|publisher=''[[TV Guide]]''|accessdate=2008-09-29}}</ref> The Microism, from [[Wordpress]] stated that he was addicted to House.<ref name="WP"/> For his portrayal of Gregory House, Hugh Laurie has won [[Golden Globe Award for Best Performance by an Actor in a Television Series - Drama|Best Actor in a Television Drama Series]] from the [[Golden Globe Award|Golden Globe]] in 2006 and 2007, and [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Drama Series|Best Actor from Drama Series]] from [[Screen Actors Guild Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Entertainment/story?id=1512758|title=Loose Lips Backstage at Golden Globes|first=David|last=Blaustein|date=2006-01-17|work=Clooney Jokes About 'Brokeback' Sequel; Phoenix Loses $220 Betting Against Himself|publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC News]]|accessdate=2008-09-29}}</ref> Laurie also earned [[Primetime Emmy Award]] nominations in 2005, 2007 and 2008.<ref name=08emmynoms>{{cite news|publisher=''[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]''|date=2008-07-17|url=http://cdn.emmys.tv/awards/2008pte/60thpte_noms.php|title=Complete 2008 Nominations List|accessdate=2008-07-25}}</ref><ref name="07emmynoms">{{cite web |url=http://www.emmys.org/awards/2007pt/59thnominations.php |title=The 59th Primetime Emmy Awards and Creative Arts Emmy Awards Nominees are... |accessdate=2008-03-02 |publisher=''[[Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]]''}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=First Set Of Presenters Announced for the 60th Primetime Emmy Awards Airing Sunday, September 21, on ABC|url=http://cdn.emmys.tv/media/releases/2008/rel-pte60-pres1.php|date=2008-08-21|publisher=Academy of Television Arts & Sciences|accessdate=2008-09-26}}</ref>

==Notes==
<div class="references-small">
<ol type="a">
<li>{{Note_label|A|a|none}}In episode 11 of season 1, "[[Detox (House)|Detox]]", House admits that he is addicted to Vicodin. At the end of the episode, Wilson and House are discussing how House has changed since the infarction in his leg and Wilson asks, "And everything's the leg, nothing's the pills, they haven't done a thing to you?" To which House responds, "They let me do my job, and they take away my pain."</li>
